<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.0.mh" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm">Written Answers Friday 2 July 2010</major-heading>

<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.1.mh" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm">Scottish Executive</major-heading>

<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34618.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#1">Apprenticeships</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34618.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80404" speakername="David Whitton (Strathkelvin and Bearsden) (Lab)" spid="S3W-34618" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#1">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive whether it will provide a breakdown by category of the 20,000 modern apprenticeship places provided in the last year as announced on 17 March 2010.</p>

</ques>


<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34619.q1" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80404" speakername="David Whitton (Strathkelvin and Bearsden) (Lab)" spid="S3W-34619" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#1">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive whether it will provide a breakdown of the successful applicants for the &pound;1,000 offer under the Invest in an Apprentice scheme that ran from January to March 2010.</p>

</ques>


<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34620.q2" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80404" speakername="David Whitton (Strathkelvin and Bearsden) (Lab)" spid="S3W-34620" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#1">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive how much of the additional funding under the &pound;1,000 Invest in an Apprentice scheme offer that ran from January to March 2010 was given to Tesco.</p>

</ques>


<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34621.q3" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80404" speakername="David Whitton (Strathkelvin and Bearsden) (Lab)" spid="S3W-34621" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#1">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive how much of the additional funding under the &pound;1,000 Invest in an Apprentice scheme offer that ran from January to March 2010 was given to British Gas.</p>

</ques>


<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34622.q4" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80404" speakername="David Whitton (Strathkelvin and Bearsden) (Lab)" spid="S3W-34622" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#1">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive how much of the additional funding under the &pound;1,000 Invest in an Apprentice scheme offer that ran from January to March 2010 was given to Superdrug.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34622.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80289" speakername="Keith Brown" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#1">

  <p>The Scottish Government does not hold this information centrally. I will ask the Chief Executive of Skills Development Scotland to write to you with the information you have requested.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34613.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#2">Skills Development Scotland</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34613.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80404" speakername="David Whitton (Strathkelvin and Bearsden) (Lab)" spid="S3W-34613" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#2">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what agency was employed by Skills Development Scotland to devise its proposed new brand image, Scotland the Works.</p>

</ques>


<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34614.q1" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80404" speakername="David Whitton (Strathkelvin and Bearsden) (Lab)" spid="S3W-34614" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#2">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive how much was spent by Skills Development Scotland to develop the proposed new brand image, Scotland the Works.</p>

</ques>


<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34615.q2" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80404" speakername="David Whitton (Strathkelvin and Bearsden) (Lab)" spid="S3W-34615" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#2">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive how much was spent by Skills Development Scotland on its recent all-staff conference held at venues in Glasgow, Edinburgh and Aviemore; who organised the events; who authorised the expenditure, and how many staff attended.</p>

</ques>


<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34616.q3" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80404" speakername="David Whitton (Strathkelvin and Bearsden) (Lab)" spid="S3W-34616" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#2">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what company was employed to record the video message from the chief executive of Skills Development Scotland for use at its recent all-staff event; how much it cost to produce, and who authorised the expenditure.</p>

</ques>


<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34617.q4" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80404" speakername="David Whitton (Strathkelvin and Bearsden) (Lab)" spid="S3W-34617" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#2">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what plans Skills Development Scotland has to appoint two new senior directors; what areas of expertise they will have; what their salary bands will be, and when they will start work.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2010-07-02.S3W-34617.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80289" speakername="Keith Brown" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-10/wa0702.htm#2">

  <p>This is an operational matter for Skills Development Scotland. I have asked the Chief Executive to write to you with this information.</p>

</reply>


